The paper focuses on a fully-integrated sensing and control system for mobile manipulator robots to execute building tasks with millimeter-scale accuracy on construction sites. This involves leveraging multi-modal sensing capabilities for state estimation, tight integration with digital building models, and integrated trajectory planning and whole-body motion control. These topics are all related to robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), control systems (cs.SY), machine learning (cs.MA), and possibly also statistical learning (cs.LG).
